    <detaileddescription>
<para><bold>IADLXGPU1</bold> is an extension of the <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u" kindref="compound">IADLXGPU</ref> interface.<linebreak/>
 This interface provides methods to get:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>multi-GPU setup details</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>PCI bus details</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>product name of a GPU</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><table rows="4" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>InterfaceId:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>IADLXGPU1</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Smart Pointer Interface Name:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>IADLXGPU1Ptr</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherits:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u" kindref="compound">IADLXGPU</ref></para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherited By:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para>The <bold>IADLXGPU1</bold> interface is obtained from the <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u" kindref="compound">IADLXGPU</ref> interface using <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_interface__query_interface" kindref="compound">QueryInterface</ref>.</para>
<para><heading level="2">Methods </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="5" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Method   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u1__multi_g_p_u_mode" kindref="compound">MultiGPUMode</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Gets the AMD MGPU mode of a GPU.       </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u1__p_c_i_bus_lane_width" kindref="compound">PCIBusLaneWidth</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Gets the PCI bus lane width of a GPU.       </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u1__p_c_i_bus_type" kindref="compound">PCIBusType</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Gets the PCI bus type of a GPU.       </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_g_p_u1__product_name" kindref="compound">ProductName</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Gets the product name of a GPU.      </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Requirements </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Header</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>include &quot;ISystem1.h&quot;</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Minimum version</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>1.2</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Example </heading>
</para>
<para>To see how to use this interface in a C++ application, refer to the <ref refid="cpp_sample_gpus" kindref="compound">GPUs C++ sample</ref>.<linebreak/>
 For a C application, refer to the <ref refid="c_sample_gpus" kindref="compound">GPUs C sample</ref>.</para>
